<div id="review_1568188032" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1568188032" />
    <a title="shakespeareandspice" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2576681-shakespeareandspice"><img alt="shakespeareandspice" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1497035907p2/2576681.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1568188032?book_show_action=true">Mar 03, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="shakespeareandspice" class="user" itemprop="url" name="shakespeareandspice" href="/user/show/2576681-shakespeareandspice">shakespeareandspice</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780140447644" href="/book/show/14662.The_Red_and_the_Black">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2576681-shakespeareandspice?shelf=classics">classics</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2576681-shakespeareandspice?shelf=own-in-print">own-in-print</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2576681-shakespeareandspice?shelf=translated">translated</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1568188032" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2935823745731492317">What makes this novel a masterpiece is our friend Julien. Not a very likable fellow, I must admit, but a fantastically written one. He’s incredibly flawed and that’s what makes him so utterly <i>human</i>. He constantly makes horrible mistakes, trips over himself, is mostly always way in over his head, but all of that just makes him more complex, and thus more interesting.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

